Greece Being Asked to Do ‘Impossible,’ S. Africa’s Marcus Says

-- B y   A n d r e s   R .   M a r t i n e z
-- 
2011-10-07T16:58:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-07/greece-being-asked-to-do-impossible-s-africa-s-marcus-says.html
Greece  is being asked to do the
“impossible” amid the European debt crisis,  South Africa 
Reserve Bank Governor Gill Marcus said today in Johannesburg.
She said South Africa isn’t immune from global economic
concerns.  To contact the reporter on this story:
